1
00:00:35,520 --> 00:00:37,079
Hurry, there's a bridge ahead.

2
00:00:37,079 --> 00:00:37,880
Hurry up.

3
00:00:38,560 --> 00:00:39,000
Go.

4
00:00:39,240 --> 00:00:39,679
Hurry inside.

5
00:00:40,719 --> 00:00:41,079
Hurry up.

6
00:00:42,759 --> 00:00:43,159
Lao Lu.

7
00:00:47,799 --> 00:00:49,039
There's a big hole here.

8
00:00:49,880 --> 00:00:52,000
This broken bridge won't collapse, will it?

9
00:00:52,439 --> 00:00:53,359
What do we do, Commander Chen?

10
00:00:53,359 --> 00:00:54,759
We have no choice. We have no way back.

11
00:00:54,759 --> 00:00:55,359
Walk around the hole.

12
00:00:55,359 --> 00:00:56,159
Everyone, be careful.

13
00:00:56,159 --> 00:00:57,320
This essential balm... ah, good.

14
00:00:57,320 --> 00:00:58,000
I'll go first.

15
00:00:58,439 --> 00:00:59,159
Take it easy.

16
00:00:59,320 --> 00:00:59,679
Okay, let's go.

17
00:00:59,679 --> 00:01:00,520
Be careful, Lao Lu. Mr. Lu.

18
00:01:00,560 --> 00:01:00,920
Okay.

19
00:01:00,920 --> 00:01:01,840
You be careful.

20
00:01:21,879 --> 00:01:22,319
Come on.

21
00:01:34,799 --> 00:01:35,920
Lao Lu, slow down.

22
00:01:37,079 --> 00:01:37,920
You don't say.

23
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:39,280
I'd like to go faster.

24
00:01:39,280 --> 00:01:40,959
As if I could go any faster!

25
00:01:41,040 --> 00:01:42,359
Almost fell off.

26
00:01:44,439 --> 00:01:45,519
This broken bridge.

27
00:01:45,640 --> 00:01:47,920
Is this even meant for people to walk on?

28
00:01:54,959 --> 00:01:55,760
Here.

29
00:02:01,439 --> 00:02:02,200
Dawei.

30
00:02:03,640 --> 00:02:04,560
Hurry up.

31
00:02:05,120 --> 00:02:06,920
I've found the pattern now.

32
00:02:07,200 --> 00:02:08,280
This bridge,

33
00:02:10,120 --> 00:02:11,080
even though it's broken,

34
00:02:11,479 --> 00:02:12,360
it has a pattern.

35
00:02:12,840 --> 00:02:15,400
You just step where there are planks.

36
00:02:16,199 --> 00:02:16,599
Look.

37
00:02:17,120 --> 00:02:17,520
It's fine.

38
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:19,599
And don't step where there are no planks.

39
00:02:19,960 --> 00:02:21,159
Even Fatty made it across.

40
00:02:21,159 --> 00:02:21,479
We...

41
00:02:22,879 --> 00:02:23,479
Lao Lu!

42
00:02:24,199 --> 00:02:24,800
Lao Lu!

43
00:02:27,800 --> 00:02:29,039
Old Chen!

44
00:02:29,240 --> 00:02:30,360
Old Chen!

45
00:02:32,120 --> 00:02:32,680
Lao Lu!

46
00:02:32,759 --> 00:02:33,479
Mr. Lu!

47
00:02:41,520 --> 00:02:42,759
You guys hold on tight. I'll go, I'll go save him.

48
00:02:43,080 --> 00:02:43,919
Fatty, no.

49
00:02:44,080 --> 00:02:45,080
The bridge can't take the weight.

50
00:02:45,319 --> 00:02:46,039
I'll go.

51
00:02:47,639 --> 00:02:48,639
Take it easy.

52
00:02:54,879 --> 00:02:56,159
Hang in there, Lao Lu!

53
00:02:56,719 --> 00:02:57,479
Be careful!

54
00:02:59,599 --> 00:03:00,039
Come on.

55
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:03,159
Hurry up!

56
00:03:16,080 --> 00:03:16,840
Hold on tight.

57
00:03:27,759 --> 00:03:29,000
Run, hurry!

58
00:03:49,719 --> 00:03:50,120
Lao Lu!

59
00:03:50,400 --> 00:03:50,840
Come here.

60
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:56,639
Old Chen, come here quickly!

61
00:03:56,879 --> 00:03:57,840
Leave it to me.

62
00:03:59,520 --> 00:04:00,520
Fatty, hurry up and go!

63
00:04:00,919 --> 00:04:01,960
The bridge is going to collapse!

64
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:41,839
Darn it

65
00:04:42,160 --> 00:04:43,160
These clouds...

66
00:04:43,199 --> 00:04:45,639
They're gathering way too fast.

67
00:04:46,160 --> 00:04:49,560
We hurried, but still couldn't beat the clouds.

68
00:04:49,839 --> 00:04:50,759
It feels like...

69
00:04:51,079 --> 00:04:52,560
...we've been struggling for so long...

70
00:04:52,720 --> 00:04:54,240
...only to do it all in vain.

71
00:04:55,439 --> 00:04:57,720
I wanted "A view that dwarfs the peaks,"

72
00:04:58,040 --> 00:05:00,319
but now we're "Lost in the clouds."

73
00:05:02,040 --> 00:05:03,079
I don't think so.

74
00:05:03,680 --> 00:05:05,800
Staff Officer He, what's your brilliant idea?

75
00:05:05,920 --> 00:05:06,959
I think we've already found...

76
00:05:06,959 --> 00:05:08,000
...the location of the Dragon's Halo.

77
00:05:14,879 --> 00:05:16,240
Guyu stretches on endlessly.

78
00:05:16,439 --> 00:05:17,720
The hills are chaotic,

79
00:05:17,800 --> 00:05:19,360
making it hard to tell host from guest.

80
00:05:19,439 --> 00:05:20,600
It's hard to distinguish true from false.

81
00:05:20,879 --> 00:05:22,800
The secondary features seem to overshadow the main ones.

82
00:05:23,319 --> 00:05:25,160
Presumably, within this Water Dragon Vortex,

83
00:05:25,920 --> 00:05:27,480
the terrain should be even lower.

84
00:05:27,920 --> 00:05:30,040
Sitting low is like "A view from a well."

85
00:05:30,160 --> 00:05:33,160
The atmosphere lacks dignity and appears mostly humble.

86
00:05:34,839 --> 00:05:37,160
So, at the lock of this Dragon Vein,

87
00:05:37,360 --> 00:05:40,480
they built a Nine-Bend Formation Facing the Mountain.

88
00:05:43,199 --> 00:05:45,399
Although we haven't seen the terrain yet,

89
00:05:45,600 --> 00:05:47,519
the place where the fog gathers first...

90
00:05:47,600 --> 00:05:49,439
...should be where the Water Dragon Vortex is.

91
00:05:50,560 --> 00:05:51,399
Let's take a break.

92
00:05:54,160 --> 00:05:55,160
I get it now.

93
00:05:55,600 --> 00:05:58,240
The place where the fog gathers first...

94
00:05:58,240 --> 00:06:00,319
...is the lowest point of the terrain.

95
00:06:00,399 --> 00:06:04,879
And the lowest point is where the tomb is located.

96
00:06:04,959 --> 00:06:06,800
How... How was my phrasing there?

97
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:08,399
"Where the tomb is located."

98
00:06:11,439 --> 00:06:12,120
However,

99
00:06:12,720 --> 00:06:15,480
you only gave a general location.

100
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:18,000
How do we find the exact spot?

101
00:06:18,759 --> 00:06:20,480
Didn't I tell you on the way?

102
00:06:20,480 --> 00:06:23,120
The ninth Acupoint is closest to the core area.

103
00:06:23,120 --> 00:06:24,839
Let's set a general direction first.

104
00:06:24,839 --> 00:06:25,759
Head west.

105
00:06:25,920 --> 00:06:27,720
Just look for the Mountain God Temple on the way.

106
00:06:28,959 --> 00:06:30,360
Right, exactly.

107
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:31,959
I finally understand.

108
00:06:31,959 --> 00:06:34,959
This ninth Acupoint is the most important.

109
00:06:35,079 --> 00:06:36,800
We've found one now.

110
00:06:37,560 --> 00:06:40,040
The rest is just finding the other eight.

111
00:06:42,720 --> 00:06:43,439
By finding one,

112
00:06:43,439 --> 00:06:45,360
we've already deduced its location.

113
00:06:45,560 --> 00:06:47,240
Why do you need to find the other eight?

114
00:06:48,199 --> 00:06:49,000
Fatty,

115
00:06:49,199 --> 00:06:51,120
even I understood it, but you didn't.

116
00:06:51,639 --> 00:06:52,480
Oh, come on.

117
00:06:52,600 --> 00:06:53,800
Don't you get the logic?

118
00:06:53,800 --> 00:06:55,120
It's like eating steamed buns.

119
00:06:55,120 --> 00:06:56,000
If five make you full,

120
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:57,199
you can't just skip the first four.

121
00:06:58,079 --> 00:06:58,759
Seriously.

122
00:06:59,600 --> 00:07:00,480
In my opinion,

123
00:07:01,319 --> 00:07:02,839
we won't find this Mountain God Temple at all.

124
00:07:03,639 --> 00:07:04,600
Let me tell you,

125
00:07:04,759 --> 00:07:06,000
you can mock me,

126
00:07:06,480 --> 00:07:08,000
but who is our Lao Chen?

127
00:07:08,439 --> 00:07:10,839
Eight generations of a Feng Shui family.

128
00:07:10,879 --> 00:07:12,639
What he says is definitely right.

129
00:07:12,920 --> 00:07:14,519
Then Fatty, let me ask you.

130
00:07:15,120 --> 00:07:17,560
Are there a lot of bugs in this valley?

131
00:07:17,560 --> 00:07:19,120
Can you please not mention the bugs?

132
00:07:19,240 --> 00:07:20,439
It makes me itch all over.

133
00:07:20,480 --> 00:07:21,319
Then let me ask you again.

134
00:07:21,319 --> 00:07:23,920
Is the humidity high in this valley?

135
00:07:23,920 --> 00:07:25,399
What kind of terrain is this?

136
00:07:25,680 --> 00:07:26,480
A rainforest.

137
00:07:26,879 --> 00:07:28,160
What do you think about the humidity?

138
00:07:28,319 --> 00:07:29,040
Exactly.

139
00:07:29,199 --> 00:07:30,920
Exposed to the sun and rain for so long,

140
00:07:31,120 --> 00:07:33,800
that temple must be a pile of rotten wood by now.

141
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:35,000
Furthermore,

142
00:07:35,360 --> 00:07:36,920
even if it hasn't rotted or been eaten by bugs,

143
00:07:37,199 --> 00:07:39,720
the surrounding vegetation has grown wildly for over a thousand years.

144
00:07:39,839 --> 00:07:41,519
Unless you have X-ray vision,

145
00:07:41,560 --> 00:07:43,519
otherwise, I don't think we'll find it at all.

146
00:07:44,360 --> 00:07:46,120
Look at him.

147
00:07:48,160 --> 00:07:49,600
You really are a great tomb...

148
00:07:51,879 --> 00:07:52,480
Tomb...

149
00:07:52,839 --> 00:07:54,120
...archaeology prospect.

150
00:07:56,439 --> 00:07:59,199
To ensure the Feng Shui in Guyu remains continuous,

151
00:07:59,600 --> 00:08:01,839
the Mountain God Temple must be guaranteed not to rot for a thousand years.

152
00:08:03,360 --> 00:08:04,120
Shutong,

153
00:08:04,560 --> 00:08:05,959
show me the drawing you just made.

154
00:08:13,319 --> 00:08:15,279
Local areas in Guyu have erratic winds.

155
00:08:15,279 --> 00:08:16,360
But this place is affected

156
00:08:16,360 --> 00:08:18,839
by the Indian Ocean southwest monsoon all year.

157
00:08:18,839 --> 00:08:20,439
The windward slope of the mountain is in the southwest.

158
00:08:20,439 --> 00:08:22,839
So the Mountain God Temple won't be built in the southwest.

159
00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:26,879
Most insects in the valley prefer dark and damp places.

160
00:08:26,959 --> 00:08:28,319
To avoid insect damage,

161
00:08:28,439 --> 00:08:30,839
the Mountain God Temple won't be built on the shady side.

162
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:33,200
This place has plenty of sunlight and rain.

163
00:08:33,279 --> 00:08:34,000
Plants grow wildly.

164
00:08:34,039 --> 00:08:35,200
To prevent the Mountain God Temple

165
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:36,799
from being crushed by surrounding vegetation,

166
00:08:36,799 --> 00:08:38,840
it must be built in an area covered with shrubs

167
00:08:38,919 --> 00:08:40,039
rather than tall trees.

168
00:08:40,159 --> 00:08:41,200
Groundwater levels and terrain

169
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:42,759
are also important factors to consider.

170
00:08:42,799 --> 00:08:45,159
So it must be built in a place with good drainage

171
00:08:45,159 --> 00:08:46,600
that isn't prone to waterlogging.

172
00:08:46,919 --> 00:08:48,279
To avoid flood disasters,

173
00:08:49,039 --> 00:08:51,399
so we can only go to this place.

174
00:08:53,120 --> 00:08:55,039
Bro, you're amazing.

175
00:08:55,399 --> 00:08:56,919
Once you add these conditions,

176
00:08:56,919 --> 00:08:58,159
the scope is narrowed down a lot.

177
00:08:58,879 --> 00:09:00,000
Don't celebrate too early.

178
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:01,919
The narrowed scope is only relative.

179
00:09:02,840 --> 00:09:03,519
Thanks.

180
00:09:20,679 --> 00:09:21,840
There's an ant nest here.

181
00:09:22,480 --> 00:09:23,960
Sister Shutong, did you know?

182
00:09:23,960 --> 00:09:26,039
Inside this ant nest, there is

183
00:09:26,159 --> 00:09:27,120
there is a queen ant.

184
00:09:27,399 --> 00:09:29,000
The rest are worker ants. What does that mean?

185
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:30,679
If it were me, I couldn't stand it.

186
00:09:30,679 --> 00:09:31,799
I don't know about your temper.

187
00:09:32,320 --> 00:09:34,360
Are you questioning my strength?

188
00:09:35,039 --> 00:09:35,879
Have you ever had any?

189
00:09:35,960 --> 00:09:36,879
Do I not?

190
00:09:37,120 --> 00:09:37,799
Do you?

191
00:09:38,720 --> 00:09:40,080
I must have at least a little.

192
00:11:00,879 --> 00:11:01,519
Lao Chen.

193
00:11:01,960 --> 00:11:03,519
Is this path reliable?

194
00:11:04,120 --> 00:11:05,080
We've been walking for so long,

195
00:11:05,080 --> 00:11:06,360
and we haven't seen a single trace.

196
00:11:06,720 --> 00:11:07,000
What's wrong?

197
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:08,720
If you don't trust me, don't you trust the compass?

198
00:11:09,679 --> 00:11:10,440
Are you doing this on purpose

199
00:11:10,440 --> 00:11:12,200
to make me lose face in front of everyone?

200
00:11:12,720 --> 00:11:13,519
Look.

201
00:11:13,919 --> 00:11:15,039
There's a rock over there.

202
00:11:34,879 --> 00:11:36,000
Don't go any further.

203
00:11:37,200 --> 00:11:38,159
I think,

204
00:11:38,679 --> 00:11:40,120
in the middle of nowhere like this,

205
00:11:40,120 --> 00:11:41,559
a big rock appearing here

206
00:11:41,840 --> 00:11:42,960
is very abrupt.

207
00:11:43,399 --> 00:11:45,039
Could it be some kind of trap?

208
00:11:46,039 --> 00:11:48,000
There's an eye shape on it.

209
00:11:56,159 --> 00:11:56,679
Lao Chen.

210
00:12:20,360 --> 00:12:21,679
Isn't this strange?

211
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:23,679
Exposed to the wind and sun,

212
00:12:23,919 --> 00:12:25,679
how come this big eye on the rock

213
00:12:25,679 --> 00:12:27,559
doesn't fade?

214
00:12:28,279 --> 00:12:29,720
Don't you know a lot?

215
00:12:30,840 --> 00:12:32,039
Back in the Dian King's time,

216
00:12:32,120 --> 00:12:33,399
were there any pigments

217
00:12:33,519 --> 00:12:35,360
that could remain unchanged for a thousand years?

218
00:12:36,440 --> 00:12:38,600
The pigments used in the Han Dynasty,

219
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:39,679
yes.

220
00:12:40,080 --> 00:12:41,159
Like ochre,

221
00:12:41,440 --> 00:12:42,559
Madder,

222
00:12:42,759 --> 00:12:43,960
sappanwood.

223
00:12:44,639 --> 00:12:45,840
But these things,

224
00:12:45,879 --> 00:12:48,279
they can't last a thousand years without fading.

225
00:12:48,320 --> 00:12:49,200
Not to mention,

226
00:12:49,279 --> 00:12:51,279
it has no protective measures at all.

227
00:12:51,840 --> 00:12:53,200
Just left out like this,

228
00:12:54,360 --> 00:12:55,840
it hasn't faded at all.

229
00:12:55,879 --> 00:12:57,080
Bright as new.

230
00:12:58,480 --> 00:12:59,279
Incredible.

231
00:12:59,759 --> 00:13:02,679
Could it have been made by later generations?

232
00:13:03,120 --> 00:13:03,960
Later generations?

233
00:13:04,320 --> 00:13:05,519
The Dian King's descendants?

234
00:13:06,360 --> 00:13:07,399
It's possible.

235
00:13:08,679 --> 00:13:11,840
But with this big eyeball placed here,

236
00:13:12,200 --> 00:13:14,120
what does it actually mean?

237
00:13:16,440 --> 00:13:18,159
What else could it mean?

238
00:13:18,759 --> 00:13:21,519
Wherever the Lingxiao Pearl is, there's this eye pattern.

239
00:13:21,759 --> 00:13:22,759
Doesn't this prove

240
00:13:22,759 --> 00:13:24,840
that the Lingxiao Pearl must be in the Dian King's Tomb?
